After an ugly first half, the Wolverines took it to Michigan State to secure a season sweep and a shot at their second consecutive Big Ten Tournament title.
Critically, Simpson did a lot of his best work in the first half as the rest of the team scuffled on offense.
Beilein ran much of the offense through Wagner to open the second half, and he responded with five points in five minutes.
According to KenPom, Michigan delivered the third-best defensive performance against MSU this season.
They're 0-2 against Michigan and 29-2 against everyone else.
